sheepdog.blueprint¶

Defines the sheepdog blueprint, which must be initialized with modules defining the data dicitonary and the data models.

create_blueprint(dictionary_to_use, models_to_use)¶

Create the blueprint.

Parameters:
  • dictionary_to_use – data dictionary such as gdcdictionary
  • models_to_use – data model such as gen3datamodel
Returns:

the sheepdog blueprint
Return type:

flask.Blueprint

sheepdog.blueprint.routes¶

List routes to be added to the blueprint in sheepdog.blueprint. Each route is constructed with the new_route function from sheepdog.blueprint.routes.route_utils.

new_route(rule, view_func, endpoint=None, methods=None, options=None)¶

Construct a dictionary representation of a URL rule to be added to the blueprint.

Parameters:
  • rule (str) – the path for the URL
  • view_func (callable) – function to render the page
Keyword Arguments:
 
  • endpoint (str) – endpoint name (internal Flask usage)
  • methods (list[str]) – list of methods the rule should handle (GET, etc.)
  • options (dict) – options to pass as keyword args to add_url_rule
Returns:

dictionary containing the above information for the route
Return type:

dict

root_create()¶

/ PUT POST PATCH

Register a program.

The content of the request is a JSON containing the information describing a program. Authorization for registering programs is limited to administrative users.

Reqheader Content-Type:
 |reqheader_Content-Type|
Reqheader Accept:
 |reqheader_Accept|
Reqheader X-Auth-Token:
 |reqheader_X-Auth-Token|
Resheader Content-Type:
 |resheader_Content-Type|
Statuscode 200:Registered successfully.
Statuscode 404:Program not found.
Statuscode 403:Unauthorized request.

Example:

POST /v0/submission/CGCI/ HTTP/1.1
Host: example.com
Content-Type: application/json
X-Auth-Token: MIIDKgYJKoZIhvcNAQcC...
Accept: application/json

{
    "type": "program",
    "name": "CGCI",
    "dbgap_accession_number": "phs000178"
}

close_transaction(program, project, *args, **kwargs)¶

Close a transaction. The transaction is prevented from being committed in the future.

commit_dry_run_transaction(program, project, *args, **kwargs)¶

See documentation for committing a dry run transaction.

This call should only succeed if: 1. transaction_id points to a dry_run transaction 2. transaction_id points to a transaction that hasn’t been committed already 3. transaction_id points to a successful transaction

create_viewer(method, bulk=False, dry_run=False)¶

Provide view functions for the following endpoints:

/<program>/<project> /<program>/<project>/_dry_run /<program>/<project>/bulk /<program>/<project>/bulk/_dry_run

for POST and PUT methods.

The view function returned is for handling either a POST or PUT method and with dry_run being either True or False.

export_entities(program, project, *args, **kwargs)¶

Export endpoint which returns a file with required entities as an attachment.

Query ids:one or a list of gdc ids seperated by comma
Query format:output format, json or tsv or csv, default is tsv
Query with_children:
 recursively find children or not. True or False, default is False
Query category:category of node to filter on children. Example: clinical

If there is only one entity type in the output, it will return a {node_type}.tsv or {node_type}.json, eg: aliquot.tsv If there are multiple entity types, it returns gdc_export_{one_time_sha}.tar.gz for tsv format, returns gdc_export_{one_time_sha}.json for json format

:statuscode 200 Success :statuscode 400 Bad Request :statuscode 404 No id is found :statuscode 403 Unauthorized

get_entities_by_id(program, *args, **kwargs)¶

Retrieve existing GDC entities by ID.

The return type of a :http:method:`get` on this endpoint is a JSON array containing JSON object elements, each corresponding to a provided ID. Return results are unordered.

If any ID is not found in the database, a status code of 404 is returned with the missing IDs.

Parameters:
  • program (str) – |program_id|
  • project (str) – |project_id|
  • entity_id_string (str) – A comma-separated list of ids specifying the entities to retrieve.
Reqheader Content-Type:
 

|reqheader_Content-Type|
Reqheader Accept:
 

|reqheader_Accept|
Reqheader X-Auth-Token:
 

|reqheader_X-Auth-Token|
Resheader Content-Type:
 

|resheader_Content-Type|
Statuscode 200:

Success.
Statuscode 404:

Entity not found.
Statuscode 403:

Unauthorized request.

get_project_template(program, project, *args, **kwargs)¶

Return TSV template of an entity type.

In the template, links are represented as {link_type}.{link_unique_key} for one_to_one and many_to_one relationships. For many_to_many relationships, they are represented as {link_type}.{link_unique_key}#1 to infer user the multiplicity.

Parameters:
  • program (str) – |program_id|
  • project (str) – |project_id|
  • entity (str) – type of the entity
Query format:

output format, csv or tsv, default is tsv

:statuscode 200 Success :statuscode 404 Entity type is not found

get_project_templates(program, project, *args, **kwargs)¶

Get templates for all entity types.

In the template, Links are represented as {link_type}.{link_unique_key} for one_to_one and many_to_one relationships. For many_to_many relationships, they are represented as {link_type}.{link_unique_key}#1 to infer user the multiplicity

Parameters:
  • program (str) – |program_id|
  • project (str) – |project_id|
Query format:

output format, csv or tsv, default is tsv
Query categories:
 

target entities’ categories
Query exclude:

entity types to be excluded

:statuscode 200 Success
